Subject: finger
Index: ucb/finger.c 4.3BSD

When one "fingers" someone on a SUN, especially a personal one,
one often gets several screenfuls of output, corresponding to
various shells the user has created.  This suggests that there should be
an option to "finger" which shows, for each user, only the login with
the least idle time.
			Yours,		George Bergman
